# Goal
Upgrade the session creation form to use TanStack Form with Zod validation for better UX and maintainability.

## Background
The session creation form (/sessions/new) has 4 fields:
- Thread ID (required, unique identifier format)
- Hypothesis (required, text)
- Prior Beliefs (required, text)
- Target Agent (required, selection)

Current implementation uses native HTML form with server action:
```typescript
<form action={sendKickoff}>
  <Input name="threadId" required />
  <Textarea name="hypothesis" required />
  <Textarea name="priors" required />
  <select name="agent" required>...</select>
  <button type="submit">Send Kickoff</button>
</form>
```

Issues:
1. No client-side validation
2. No field-level error display
3. No dirty/pristine tracking
4. Submit button doesn't disable during submission

## Implementation

### 1. Define Zod schema
```typescript
import { z } from 'zod';

const sessionSchema = z.object({
  threadId: z.string()
    .min(1, 'Thread ID is required')
    .regex(/^[A-Z]+-\d+$/, 'Format: FEAT-123'),
  hypothesis: z.string()
    .min(10, 'Hypothesis must be at least 10 characters'),
  priors: z.string()
    .min(10, 'Prior beliefs must be at least 10 characters'),
  agent: z.enum(['opus', 'gpt', 'gemini'], {
    errorMap: () => ({ message: 'Select a target agent' }),
  }),
});

type SessionFormData = z.infer<typeof sessionSchema>;
```

### 2. Create form with TanStack Form
```typescript
import { useForm } from '@tanstack/react-form';
import { zodValidator } from '@tanstack/zod-form-adapter';

function SessionForm() {
  const form = useForm({
    defaultValues: {
      threadId: '',
      hypothesis: '',
      priors: '',
      agent: '' as const,
    },
    onSubmit: async ({ value }) => {
      await mutation.mutateAsync(value);
    },
    validatorAdapter: zodValidator(),
  });

  return (
    <form
      onSubmit={(e) => {
        e.preventDefault();
        form.handleSubmit();
      }}
    >
      <form.Field
        name="threadId"
        validators={{ onChange: sessionSchema.shape.threadId }}
      >
        {(field) => (
          <div>
            <Input
              value={field.state.value}
              onChange={(e) => field.handleChange(e.target.value)}
              onBlur={field.handleBlur}
            />
            {field.state.meta.errors.length > 0 && (
              <span className="text-destructive text-sm">
                {field.state.meta.errors.join(', ')}
              </span>
            )}
          </div>
        )}
      </form.Field>

      {/* Similar for other fields */}

      <form.Subscribe
        selector={(state) => [state.canSubmit, state.isSubmitting]}
      >
        {([canSubmit, isSubmitting]) => (
          <button type="submit" disabled={!canSubmit || isSubmitting}>
            {isSubmitting ? 'Sending...' : 'Send Kickoff'}
          </button>
        )}
      </form.Subscribe>
    </form>
  );
}
```

## Features Enabled

### Field-Level Validation
Each field validates on change/blur with immediate feedback.

### Form-Level State
- canSubmit: All validations pass
- isSubmitting: Async submission in progress
- isDirty: Any field changed from initial
- isTouched: Any field has been focused

